Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest

SpineDigest CLI

Purpose:
  Distill long-form EPUB, Markdown, or plain text into compressed output.
  Digesting source input uses an LLM pipeline. Re-opening an existing .sdpub archive does not.

Usage:
  spinedigest [--input <path>] [--output <path>] [--input-format <format>] [--output-format <format>] [--digest-dir <path>] [--prompt <text>] [--verbose|-v] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest sdpub <subcommand> --input <path> [--serial <id>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest help [topic] [--help|-h]

Help contract:
  - Append `--help` to any command or subcommand to see its command-specific usage.
  - Use `spinedigest help <topic>` for cross-command concepts, constraints, and runtime behavior.
  - Treat `spinedigest --help` as the root page of the same help system.

Flag aliases:
  - `-h` is the short form of `--help` on every command and subcommand.
  - `-v` is the short form of `--verbose` on the main convert command.

Common paths:
  Source input -> digest -> markdown | txt | epub | .sdpub
  .sdpub input -> re-export or inspect without re-running the digest pipeline

